title: Committee on Promotion of Organ Donation holds meeting (with photo)
content_text:
p>
					The Committee on Promotion of Organ Donation held its second 
					meeting today (September 29) to review the progress of the 
					promotion of organ donation and discuss the upcoming 
					promotional plan with the view to encouraging more people to 
					support organ donation. The Chairperson of the Committee and the Under Secretary for 
					Food and Health, Professor Sophia Chan, said, "The 
					Government launched the Organ Donation Promotion Charter in 
					June this year and invited different organisations,

June this year and invited different organisations, 
					corporations and schools to indicate their support on 
					promotion of organ donation and appeal to the public to 
					register their wish of donating their organs on the 
					Centralised Organ Donation Register managed by the 
					Department of Health. There are over 180 signatories of the 
					said Charter so far. "These signatories have been organising various promotional 
					activities, such as distributing promotional leaflets,

activities, such as distributing promotional leaflets, 
					producing videos. Some of them have set up working groups to 
					study how to further promote the culture of organ donation, 
					encourage their staff or members to register their wish to 
					donate organs, further solicit support from the family 
					members of their staff or members and help promote the 
					culture in the community. "With the view to further stepping up the promotion on organ 
					donation, the Government will introduce large scale

donation, the Government will introduce large scale 
					promotional work in the coming months, including cooperating 
					with the Mass Transit Railway Corporation Limited on 
					organising large scale promotional activities and conduct a 
					bus parade to invite more members of the public to get 
					familiarised and accept the concept of organ donation." At the meeting, the members of the Committee expressed views 
					on issues such as how to further improve the promotional 
					work on organ donation. They are of the view that the

work on organ donation. They are of the view that the 
					Government may consider enhancing the support provided to 
					different organisations in conducting activities promoting 
					organ donation and to make better use of the Internet and 
					social media to disseminate the information on organ 
					donation, and to encourage the public to register their wish 
					at the CODR immediately. The Food and Health Bureau, the Department of Health and the 
					Hospital Authority will thoroughly study the recommendations 
					proposed by the members and continue working with different

proposed by the members and continue working with different 
					parties in the society to enhance the promotion on organ 
					donation. Setting up by the Government in April this year, the 
					Committee comprises members from relevant professional 
					organisations and non-governmental organisations, as well as 
					media partners. The membership list of the Committee is as
